        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add accessible Workboard movement controls",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add a compact writable-only Workboard card status control that moves cards through the existing `workboard.cards.move` path.\n- Support keyboard movement with the native status menu plus focused `ArrowLeft` / `ArrowRight` shortcuts, while preserving drag/drop as the pointer enhancement.\n- Cover read-only suppression, select-change movement, keyboard-arrow movement, and update the Workboard workflow docs.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts`\n- `corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 ui/src/ui/views/workboard.ts ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts ui/src/styles/workboard.css docs/plugins/workboard.md`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- Playwright browser proof on the mock Control UI: Tabbed to the Workboard status control, pressed `ArrowRight`, observed `workboard.cards.move` with `status: \"scheduled\"`, reloaded, and confirmed the card remained visible under Scheduled.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Keyboard-only Workboard operators can move a card to another status without opening a modal; read-only operators still cannot mutate cards.\nReal environment tested: Local Vite Control UI with the repo mock Gateway in Playwright Chromium.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Loaded `/workboard`, tabbed to `.workboard-card__move-select`, pressed `ArrowRight`, waited for `workboard.cards.move`, reloaded with the moved card returned by `workboard.cards.list`.\nEvidence after fix: The mock Gateway recorded `{ \"id\": \"card-keyboard-proof\", \"status\": \"scheduled\", \"position\": 1000 }`; after reload, the card rendered in the Scheduled column.\nObserved result after fix: The movement persisted through the Workboard move endpoint and remained visible after refresh.\nWhat was not tested: Full production Gateway persistence beyond the existing `workboard.cards.move` contract; the browser proof used the repo mock Gateway.\n",
